  "entity": {
    "name": "Norse - Loki",
    "mythology": "norse",
    "type": "deity",
    "icon": "üé≠",
    "subtitle": "The Trickster, Agent of Chaos",
    "description": "The shapeshifter and trickster who dwells among the gods despite being a giant's son. Blood-brother to <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Odin\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=odin\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Odin'\">Odin</a>, <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Father of Monsters\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Father of Monsters'\">father of monsters</a>, helper and betrayer of the Aesir. His cunning brings both salvation and doom to the gods, culminating in the death of <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a> and his binding until <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Ragnarok\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=ragnarok\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Ragnarok'\">Ragnarok</a>.",
    "css_colors": {}
  },
  "attributes": {},
  "mythology_stories": {
    "intro": "<a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a> is the most complex and contradictory figure in Norse mythology - neither fully evil nor good, neither god nor giant, but something in between. He is a necessary force of chaos that tests the gods and pushes them to adapt, but ultimately his role leads to the destruction of the cosmos at <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Ragnarok\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=ragnarok\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Ragnarok'\">Ragnarok</a>.",
    "key_myths": [
      {
        "name": "Birth of Sleipnir",
        "description": "When a giant builder threatened to complete <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Asgard\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=asgard\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Asgard'\">Asgard</a>'s walls, <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a> transformed into a mare to lure away the giant's stallion Svadilfari. Later, <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a> gave birth to the eight-legged horse Sleipnir, which became <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Odin\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=odin\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Odin'\">Odin</a>'s mount."
      },
      {
        "name": "The Death ofBaldr",
        "description": "<strong>The Death of <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a>:</strong> <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a>'s greatest crime. He discovered that mistletoe was the only thing that could harm <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a> and tricked the blind god Hod into throwing it, killing the most beloved of the gods. When <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Hel\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=hel\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Hel'\">Hel</a> offered to release <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a> if all things wept for him, <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a> disguised himself as a giantess and refused to weep, sealing <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a>'s fate."
      },
      {
        "name": "The Binding ofLoki",
        "description": "<strong>The Binding of <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a>:</strong> As punishment for <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a>'s death, the gods bound <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a> to three rocks with the entrails of his son Nari. A serpent was placed above him to drip venom on his face. His wife Sigyn holds a bowl to catch the venom, but when she must empty it, the venom falls on <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a>, causing him to writhe in agony - these convulsions cause earthquakes."
      },
      {
        "name": "The Treasures of the Gods",
        "description": "After cutting off Sif's golden hair as a prank, <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a> commissioned the dwarves to create replacement hair and other treasures, including <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Thor's Hammer\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=mjolnir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Thor's Hammer'\">Thor's hammer</a> <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Mjolnir\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=mjolnir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Mjolnir'\">Mjolnir</a>, <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Odin's Spear\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=gungnir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Odin's Spear'\">Odin's spear</a> <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Gungnir\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=gungnir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Gungnir'\">Gungnir</a>, and <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Freyr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=freyr\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Freyr'\">Freyr</a>'s ship Skidbladnir."
      }
    ],
    "sources": "Poetic Edda (Lokasenna, V√∂lusp√°), Prose Edda (Gylfaginning)"
  },
